              <div class="quotetitle">Pocky Is God wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What yeast? I want to do something similar along the lines of Le Freak from Greenflash with the Wyeast Ardennes yeast. I want some phenols in there, and that yeast is good for very high ABV. I also want to use New Zealand hops because I am in love with Nelson Sauvin hops...</div><br /><br />White Labs WLP500 yeast. It is supposedly cloned from Chimay yeast. My fermentation temperature is going to be a little on the low side, so I don't think I'll get the full ester/phenol profile, which might not necessarily be a bad thing.

              

              
              
