        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Ok, I've been on brewing hiatus for a while.  I'm getting back into the mix soon.  Going to ease back into it with a few extract / partial mash batches, and eventually build a mash tun out of a big ass Igloo cooler.  But I have a question for now.  I want to do a &quot;coffee milk stout&quot; .. which shouldn't be too difficult .. there are plenty of extract kits / recipes for this.  Here's the twist though .. I want a little bit of sweetness left over, or maybe I need to backsweeten it a bit.  I don't want super sweet, but I do want to retain a little bit of sweetness.  Should I boil some dextrose in H20 and throw it in the primary, in order to accomplish this feat?

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
