          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              I've got a weird issue with my Steam Bock.  If you look at a bottle that's been sitting still for a while, it's crystal clear (except for the one in the fridge which has some mild chill haze).  However, if you pick up the bottle and jostle/swirl it, some flakes kick up off the bottom and float in suspension, but eventually settle back down to the bottom.  I don't think it's yeast, it looks more like little pieces of hops or grain husks.  Like I said, it's little flakes of something.<br /><br />Looking at my notes, this is with Wyeast 2112 (California Common), and it looks like I did 3 weeks in primary and then straight to bottles rather than a transfer to secondary, so I might have kicked up some trub when I racked to the bottling bucket.<br /><br />Any idea how to poor these bottles?  There isn't that much stuff that floats per bottle, so it doesn't get cloudy or anything, but it's enough to be noticeable.  I was thinking of pouring through a fine mesh tea strainer, but I'm worried that might cause carbonation issues.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
