              <a href="http://draftmag.com/mm/6205" class="postlink" rel="nofollow">March Madness for Beer</a> Bracket<br /><br />Add Isinglass to the secondary and let it cool down to below 60Â° (or less) and hold it for a few weeks.  Your beer will fall sparkling clear.  When you bottle it you will get less sediment and it will tend to stick to the bottom better.  <br /><br />Whilrflock is a good product but it is for coagulating protein in the brew kettle.

              

              
              
