              <div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"> So after a way-too-long hiatus I'm getting back into the game. I went to the LHBS this morning and got one of their custom-made recipe kits. (They make their own rather than just stocking the True Brew or whatever kits.) It's extract with specialty steeping grains. I got everything opened up and noticed there isn't a grain bag in the box. Rather than going back to the LHBS just for that, can I use a nylon paint strainer bag from HD / Lowes? I'm pretty sure I&quot;ve seen reference to this being done for BIAB so I'm assuming it will be fine for steeping the specialty grains. </div><br />Sure, Nylon is considered food safe, so should be fine. Plenty of people on homebrewtalk report using them. You could also go to your local fabric store and get some cheesecloth, but the nylon bag is more reusable. <img src="//cdn.arstechnica.net/civis/images/smilies/smile.png" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

              

              
              
