              <div class="quotetitle">rigeek wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So I went to HD and got a 2-pack .. and it doesn't look like it will be big enough for all my steeping grains .. I may have to go to the craft store and get some cheesecloth and fashion a bag out of that, unless I divide the grains into the 2 bags .. and even then, I'm not sure how I'll tie them shut.</div><br />I assume you got the 1 gallon size, they didn't have the 5 gallon ones? Both Lowes and HD show 5 gallon sized nylon paint strainers on there website, that'd be more than big enough for even 15lbs of grain I'd imagine. As to tying them, I've been using the same kitchen string I use to truss a roast for all manner of bag in my brewdays for years. For a big bag like that, I'd probably double it up for some additional strength and thread it in and out around the top to act like a drawstring.

              

              
              
