          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Is there a good rule on where the line between aging a beer and having it go stale lies? I know hoppy beers should be enjoyed young, and high gravity beers should age many months, but what about just normal ales? I have a Bock (with steam ale yeast) that's been in bottles almost two months and still tastes green.  I feel like it should have matured more by now.  <br /><br />Brewed at the end of December, bottled at the end of January, 1.054 down to 1.021, tastes slightly sour and I can't tell if I'm imagining the green apple flavor or not.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
